The default state of the personal sidebar should have originally been set to hidden in the 3.0 release.  It is a great new feature, but it destroys the layout of existing pages and drastically reduces the usable space on every page in a user's profile space.

I would like to recommend that it be possible to set the default state of the sidebar in user profiles.  I'm not sure how you would want to implement this.  It could be implemented as an theme option, that way it could be set profile by profile or as site wide.  Unfortunately I don't believe you have implemented any sort of "theme options" mechanism in your theme engine.

