These methods do not work in IE8, instead checking for the 'hidden' class is the way to go. Ideally we should always check for this. This does mean that any code using the raw jQuery methods to show/hide content will fail, but we don't really want to be using them anyway as setVisible is better and works in cases this fails (ask Dave T).

Currently as this is misdetecting hidden elements, not only will it falsely cause tests to fail (which is currently happening), but it could falsely cause tests to pass (which I _hope_ isn't happening). Hence the priority Major.

